ShortBio:
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;WeiWangreceivedtheB.S.andPh.D.degreesin2004and2009respectively,bothfromBeijingUniversityofPostsandTelecommunications,Beijing,P.R.China.Currently,heisanAssociateProfessorwithCollegeofInformationScienceandElectronicEngineering,ZhejiangUniversity,Hangzhou,China.FromSeptember2007toSeptember2008,hewasaVisitingStudentwithUniversityofMichigan,AnnArbor,USA.FromFebruary2013toFebruary2015,hewasaHongKongScholarwithHongKongUniversityofScienceandTechnology,HongKong.Hisresearchinterestsmainlyfocusoncognitiveradionetworks,greencommunications,andradioresourceallocationforwirelessnetworks.Hehaspublishedmorethan80internationaljournalandconferencepapersintheareaofwirelesscommunicationsandnetworks.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;HeistheAssociateSecretary-GeneralofZhejiangInstituteofCommunications,andanIEEEseniormember.HeistheeditorofthebookCognitiveRadioSystems(Intech,2009)andservesasaneditorforIEEEAccessandTransactionsonEmergingTelecommunicationsTechnologies.Healsoservesasco-chairorTPCmemberforseveralinternationalconferences.&nbsp;
